HEADWORD: Serpentry
<hw>Ser"pent*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
winding like a serpent's.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A place inhabited or infested by serpents.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Serpent-tongued</ent>⟦br⟧
